  "lead": "This week's lead is close to home: <b>Taiwan's brokerages are stampeding into the loan market</b> — 10+ firms seeking ~<b>NT$166bn (US$5.26bn)</b> in a record year, fuelled by an AI-driven equity rally that has doubled the island's market cap and pushed margin-lending demand past bank capacity. <b>CTBC Securities is leading the charge</b> and setting the pricing. But cracks are showing — single-borrower limits are binding, the thin 40bp pricing is deterring some banks, and the rally pulling deposits into stocks could tighten the very liquidity funding it.",
